From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ming Zhangqun <north_sea@qq.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] rockusb: support SD card and NVMe LUN switch in Loader mode

Allow rkdevtool to flash the SD card (SDMMC0, mmc 1) and NVMe by
switching LUNs in Loader mode. Changes in f_rockusb.c:

1. rkusb_do_switch_storage(): handle BOOT_TYPE_SD0 (mmc 1) and
   BOOT_TYPE_PCIE (nvme 0) in addition to the existing eMMC case.
   SD: mmc_initialize() then mmc 1.
   NVMe: lazy pci enum + nvme scan (running here in the rockusb main
   loop avoids a deadlock seen when called from setup_download_mode()
   during boot-early context).

2. rkusb_do_get_storage_info(): report mmc devnum 1 as BOOT_TYPE_SD0
   instead of the default BOOT_TYPE_EMMC. NVMe (IF_TYPE_NVME) is
   already mapped to BOOT_TYPE_PCIE upstream.

Signed-off-by: Ming Zhangqun <north_sea@qq.com>
---
 drivers/usb/gadget/f_rockusb.c | 30 +++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 28 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/gadget/f_rockusb.c b/drivers/usb/gadget/f_rockusb.c
--- a/drivers/usb/gadget/f_rockusb.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/gadget/f_rockusb.c
@@ -761,6 +761,11 @@
 		devnum = 0;
 		mmc_initialize(gd->bd);
 		break;
+	case BOOT_TYPE_SD0:
+		type = IF_TYPE_MMC;
+		devnum = 1;
+		mmc_initialize(gd->bd);
+		break;
 #endif
 	case BOOT_TYPE_MTD_BLK_NAND:
 		type = IF_TYPE_MTD;
@@ -786,6 +791,19 @@ static int rkusb_do_switch_storage(struct fsg_common *common)
 		scsi_scan(true);
 		break;
 #endif
+#ifdef CONFIG_NVME
+	case BOOT_TYPE_PCIE:
+		type = IF_TYPE_NVME;
+		devnum = 0;
+		/*
+		 * Lazy init: running pci enum here (in the rockusb main loop)
+		 * avoids the deadlock seen when pci enum is called from
+		 * setup_download_mode() during boot-early context.
+		 */
+		run_command("pci enum", 0);
+		run_command("nvme scan", 0);
+		break;
+#endif
 	default:
 		printf("Bootdev 0x%x is not support\n", media);
 		return -ENODEV;
@@ -832,7 +850,13 @@

 	switch (type) {
 	case IF_TYPE_MMC:
-		media = BOOT_TYPE_EMMC;
+		/* Distinguish SD card (mmc 1) from eMMC (mmc 0) by devnum,
+		 * both are registered under UCLASS_MMC with if_type=IF_TYPE_MMC.
+		 */
+		if (devnum == 1)
+			media = BOOT_TYPE_SD0;
+		else
+			media = BOOT_TYPE_EMMC;
 		break;

 	case IF_TYPE_SD:
